# M5R3

- Use only Javascript along with HTML & CSS to build this application.
- Create a form which takes following information from the user
    - Country (Select tag)
    - City
    - Population
- On form submit, post data to JSON server.
- Use JSON server to manage the data (using local storage or dummy object data will lead to disqualification)
- Fetch this data from JSON server and display in form of table as shown below

![Screenshot 2022-08-10 at 9.01.24 PM.png](https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/secure.notion-static.com/048f0384-a6cf-4a4d-9bb9-2e7e42ede90b/Screenshot_2022-08-10_at_9.01.24_PM.png)

- Users should be able to filter/sort the tabular data â†’ create select tag for filtering and sorting
    - Filter by country
    - Sort by ascending or descending population
    - Delete a city
        - when deleting a city, delete city from JSON data and display the updated data in table.

### Bonus:

- When user clicks on edit, user should be able to edit/change population of particular city in JSON data (you can use modal for this) and display updated data in table.

### Submission

- Please submit deployed link and Github link of code.
- Deploy JSON server too.
- Please double check if deployed version works or not (run deployed version on your laptop and then submit it)
- Any issues in deployed link, will be considered null and void.
- Please verify your submissions are correct.
- Make sure you follow all instructions carefully.
- Submit before deadline.

### Rubrics / Criteria to be judged upon

- CRUD Operations
- JSON server
- Fetch
- Promises
- UI
- Code cleanliness
- Usage of Javascript (using react will lead to disqualification)

**Time limit** : `150 mins`







